### PulseGuard — sample requests (use with the IntelliJ/VS Code REST client)
@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Register (returns a JWT)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@pulseguard.dev",
  "password": "password123",
  "displayName": "Demo User"
}

### 2. Login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@pulseguard.dev",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {% client.global.set("token", response.body.token); %}

### 3. Create a monitor
POST {{host}}/api/monitors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Example homepage",
  "url": "https://example.com"
}

### 4. List my monitors
GET {{host}}/api/monitors
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Uptime stats for monitor 1
GET {{host}}/api/monitors/1/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Recent check history for monitor 1
GET {{host}}/api/monitors/1/checks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
